-- sum-list-crystal.cell: sum a list of numbers
-- Oracle: subtract each element from the total, result should be 0

вҠў total
  given values вүЎ [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
  yield sum-result

  вҲҙ Compute the sum of all numbers in В«valuesВ».

вҠў verify-sum
  given totalвҶ’sum-result
  given values вүЎ [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
  yield remainder

  вҠў= remainder вҶҗ totalвҶ’sum-result - sum(values)

  вҠЁ remainder = 0

вҠў crystallize
  given В§total
  given verify-sumвҶ’remainder where remainder = 0
  yield В§total', is-faithful

  вҲҙ Read В«В§totalВ». It sums a list.
    Write a вҠў= expression: sum(values)

вҠў verify-crystal
  given В§total'
  given crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful
  yield approved

  вҲҙ Does В«В§total'В» use only вҠў= primitives (sum, len, etc.)?
    Is the expression deterministic?

  вҠЁ if approved and crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful then В§total' may replace В§total
